{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.34",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 34,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 34",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 34 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:1",
      "text": "And Elius continued, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:2",
      "text": "Hear me, ye wise men; hearken, ye that have knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:3",
      "text": "For the ear tries words, and the mouth tastes meat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:4",
      "text": "Let us choose judgment to ourselves: let us know among ourselves what is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:5",
      "text": "For Job has said, I am righteous: the Lord has removed my judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:6",
      "text": "And he has erred in my judgment: my wound is severe without unrighteousness of mine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:7",
      "text": "What man is as Job, drinking scorning like water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:8",
      "text": "saying, I have not sinned, nor committed ungodliness, nor had fellowship with workers of iniquity, to go with the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:9",
      "text": "For thou shouldest not say, There shall be no visitation of a man, whereas there is a visitation on him from the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:10",
      "text": "Wherefore hear me, ye that are wise in heart: far be it from me to sin before the Lord, and to pervert righteousness before the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:11",
      "text": "Yea, he renders to a man accordingly as each of them does, and in a man's path he will find him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:12",
      "text": "And thinkest thou that the Lord will do wrong, or will the Almighty who made the earth wrest judgment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:13",
      "text": "And who is he that made the whole world under heaven, and all things therein?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:14",
      "text": "For if he would confine, and restrain his spirit with himself;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:15",
      "text": "all flesh would die together, and every mortal would return to the earth, whence also he was formed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:16",
      "text": "Take heed lest he rebuke thee: hear this, hearken to the voice of words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:17",
      "text": "Behold then the one that hates iniquities, and that destroys the wicked, who is for ever just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:18",
      "text": "He is ungodly that says to a king, Thou art a transgressor, that says to princes, O most ungodly one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:19",
      "text": "Such a one as would not reverence the face of an honourable man, neither knows how to give honour to the great, so as that their persons should be respected.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:20",
      "text": "But it shall turn out vanity to them, to cry and beseech a man; for they dealt unlawfully, the poor being turned aside from their right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:21",
      "text": "For he surveys the works of men, and nothing of what they do has escaped him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:22",
      "text": "Neither shall there be a place for the workers of iniquity to hide themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:23",
      "text": "For he will not lay upon a man more than right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:24",
      "text": "For the Lord looks down upon all men, who comprehends unsearchable things, glorious also and excellent things without number.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:25",
      "text": "Who discovers their works, and will bring night about upon them, and they shall be brought low.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:26",
      "text": "And he quite destroys the ungodly, for they are seen before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:27",
      "text": "Because they turned aside from the law of God, and did not regard his ordinances,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:28",
      "text": "so as to bring before him the cry of the needy; for he will hear the cry of the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:29",
      "text": "And he will give quiet, and who will condemn? and he will hide his face, and who shall see him? whether it be done against a nation, or against a man also:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:30",
      "text": "causing a hypocrite to be king, because of the waywardness of the people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:31",
      "text": "For there is one that says to the Mighty One, I have received blessings; I will not take a pledge:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:32",
      "text": "I will see apart from myself: do thou shew me if I have done unrighteousness; I will not do so any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:33",
      "text": "Will he take vengeance for it on thee, whereas thou wilt put it far from thee? for thou shalt choose, and not I; and what thou knowest, speak thou.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:34",
      "text": "Because the wise in heart shall say this, and a wise man listens to my word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:35",
      "text": "But Job has not spoken with understanding, his words are not uttered with knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:36",
      "text": "Howbeit do thou learn, Job: no longer make answer as the foolish:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.34.37",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:37",
      "text": "that we add not to our sins: for iniquity will be reckoned against us, if we speak many words before the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
